  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Church Based Disaster Risk Reduction Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective #1:  To improve the knowledge of seven church member agencies in disaster response through training in hazard mapping, risk mapping and vulnerability analysis, Q&amp;amp;A standards and action planning


Objective #2:  To improve the coordination of member churches involved in disaster response through establishing an Inter-church Task Force, participating in Inter-Agency Group (IAG) meetings and developing a coordinated work plan for post-disaster efforts</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Several districts of northern Bihar State regularly experience flooding, which disproportionately impacts marginalized populations. Through its previous disaster response work, Churches Auxiliary for Social Action (CASA) has determined that churches are interested in responding to disasters but do not have the expertise to do so.

Through CASA, LWR is working to increase the engagement of church bodies in humanitarian coordination and disaster response activities in Bihar. LWR is working to improve understanding and capacity in disaster risk reduction (DRR) activities and quality and accountability (Q&amp;amp;A) standards in humanitarian
responses.

CASA plans to take the lead in involving churches in Bihar in a process of collective learning and action around emergency response and disaster preparedness.</narrative>
  </description>
